    <h3>Lore Pre-Start of Map</h3>

    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2077</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>March 21 - The Doors to Vault 79 close. Everyone left outside the vault were believed to have Perished by the nuclear war heads.</li>
        <li>October 20 - Captain Roger Maxson, now in control of Mariposa, declares himself to be in full desertion from the army (via radio)... and receives no reply.</li>
        <li>November 1 - Captain Maxson, his men, and their families, arrive at the Lost Hills bunker a few weeks later, suffering many casualties along the way,
            including Maxson's wife (but not his teenage son). The surviving soldiers go on to become the Brotherhood of Steel. (Brotherhood Of Steel is Created)</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2134</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Elder Roger Maxson dies of cancer, and his son, already an accomplished soldier,
            takes up the role of "General" (Elder) within the Brotherhood of Steel. (John Maxson becomes Brotherhood leader)</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2155</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>The Paladins, now led by Rhombus, begin a full scale campaign against the Vipers,
            tracking them down and wiping out almost all of their members within the span of a month.
            Some of the Vipers are able to flee north and east into the mountain range.</li>
        <li>Due to the campaign to wipe out the vipers, BoS squads are sent to Michigan. The squads don't find any vipers,
            but instead setup in the Michigan area keeping contact with the main BoS.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2170</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Vault 79 opens meeting the brotherhood established in the area.</li>
        <li>The Dwellers of vault 79 are completely removed from the
            vault by the BoS in an attempt to take the vault as their own.
            Vault 79 descendants spread out throughout the Michigan area.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2172</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Ericius (one of the descendants from vault 79) takes refuge in an abandoned factory.</li>
        <li>Matheson founds 'The Followers', helping sick wastelanders get better.</li>
        <li>Matheson begins his search for sapling DNA.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2173</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>War breaks out between the The Followers and local raiders called 'The League of Ordinary Gentleman'
            established in a facility on the border of Ohio and Michigan.</li>
        <li>Ericius establishes 'Ericius Enterprise' setting up caravans in Michigan.</li>
        <li>The factory becomes Ericius Enterprise Headquarters.</li>
        <li>BoS finishes turning Vault 79 into a fort.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2174</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>The Followers successfully win their war with The League of Ordinary Gentleman,
            Matheson obtaining the sapling DNA he was looking for.</li>
        <li>BoS take refuge in the The Followers hospital after being attacked by ghouls.</li>
        <li>30 days later, The The Followers kick the BoS out of the hospital,
            BoS take most of their supplies with them.</li>
        <li>10 days later, The BoS retake control of their fort..</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2175</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Rumors go around of flying machines seen going across the sky. (The BoS investigates)</li>
        <li>Mr. Ericius becomes richest man in Michigan.</li>
        <li>BoS receive T-51b power armor from the lost hills BoS headquarters.</li>
        <li>A village near the Detroit ruins begins to grow. The Village gets the name Detroit Ruins.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2176</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Detroit Ruins helps the BoS stop the ghoul attacks, in return they are awarded with 3 wind turbines.</li>
        <li>Flying machines are confirmed by the BoS in lost hills, lost hills scribe says they are
            called vertibirds by the Enclave. (BoS in Michigan stand by for further orders)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Lore Post-Start of Map</h3>

    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2177</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Enclave sets up a Citizenship Program, and Patrols, making themselves more noticeable.</li>
        <li>The Raiders continue disrupting life in Lansing.</li>
        <li>Brotherhood begins patrolling, asking the Wasters to join them to boost up numbers.</li>
        <li>A tree grows up and out of the tower of the Van Buren Medical Center, The Followers' base.</li>
        <li>The tree burns, and somewhat cripples the tower...</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2178</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>The Raiders die off a bit, only 2 members are left and disappear under other factions flags.</li>
        <li>The faction 'Survivalists' emerges, setting up in houses next to the construction crane.</li>
        <li>A new Brotherhood Elder, Elder Anlind is set temporarily.</li>
        <li>Brotherhood Elder Wotnoske returns, and the old one ends up leaving BoS joining 'Survivalists'.</li>
        <li>Enclave makes themselves more noticeable than the previous year, deaths resulted by them occur.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2179</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>A few months of peace between The Followers, Brotherhood, Enclave, and Survivalists take place.</li>
        <li>Fights against BoS and Enclave Begin from Survivalists trying to stop forced merging, and harassment.</li>
        <li>Enclaves Colonel Richards is killed by his own Men, Brotherhood and Survivalists.</li>
        <li>An Enclave soldier takes it over, named Matt, making new goals for the Enclave here, separating from Main Enclave.</li>
        <li>Matt starts research on his vault's cure 'Vault 7' for the people of his vault do not have immune systems.</li>
        <li>Brotherhood Elder Wotnoske returns to Lost Hills, sending in a new one 'Elder Michael Smith'.</li>
        <li>Brotherhood Elder Smith sets up Traditional Protocols, though keeping enlisting techniques of recruiting wasters.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2180</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Survivalists take over a Prison, after burning their old base in Lansing.</li>
        <li>BoS Elder Jake Wotnoske returns meeting Elder Smith, and Wotnoske is Demoted to Head-Paladin.</li>
        <li>Survivalists leader Jacob Reckless leaves the faction running away from his wife
            Katrina [Riordan] Reckless and 3 kids, she runs off after him with the kids.</li>
        <li>The Survivalists is taken over by Shadss Anlind (older leader of BoS
            for a time till Wotnoskes return) and renames it 'Renegades'.</li>
        <li>BoS Head Paladin Wotnoske is put under arrest for treason.</li>
        <li>BoS Head Paladin Wotnoske is killed before being
            sent to Lost Hills by Paladin James Nekros.</li>
        <li>Elder Smith receives a new Head-Paladin Ulysses Grant.</li>
        <li>Elder Smith Leaves, Grant takes over as Paladin.</li>
        <li>Matt's Enclave finds a cure for his vault 'Vault 7',
            curing the Immune System problem.</li>
        <li>Matt leaves, stealing Enclave gear.</li>
        <li>Enclave takes back base, sending in General Eden.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2181</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Matt Returns with his vaults 'Red Vipers'.</li>
        <li>Matt disappears, and Red Vipers is renamed to Faelchon under Katrina Riordans control.</li>
        <li>Renegades disbands due to fights.</li>
        <li>After a month, only 2 Renegade members are left in the Wasteland,
            and their leader Shadss Anlind returns.</li>
        <li>The Followers' hospital is destroyed and all are presumed dead.</li>
        <li>A very old member of The League of Ordinary Gentleman, Survivalists and Renegades
            'Kenneth Rim' creates a new Faction named The 'Republic of Alkali' (RoA)
            with an old member of Survivalists and Renegades 'James Collins'.</li>
        <li>Republic of Alkali begins looking for spots to set up in, finding the Detroit Ruins,
            and is allowed to set up there by its one and only resident.</li>
        <li>The Settlement of Calco rises under the Republic of Alkali's flag.</li>
        <li>Adrian Cornet comes back to the wastes not being dead after the presumption.</li>
        <li>The Brotherhood of Steel has fully pulled out taking
            any tech they could with them, and destroying the rest.</li>
        <li>The Enclave falls due to a final fight from The Republic of Alkali, and MANY energy weapons.
            Various high grade technologies are spread around, and one casualty is made.</li>
        <li>The Mayor of Calco 'Martin' dies in the Battle RoA vs Enclave.</li>
        <li>James Collins is Killed, as Vice President of RoA, and is buried.</li>
        <li>Tesla&Scarlet Industries is set up by Nikola and Scarlet.</li>
        <li>Kenneth Rim, President of The Republic of Alkali, is Assassinated.
            The Republic of Alkali falls, and all hope for the wastes being saved is lost.</li>
        <li>Various terror attacks sprawl onto Lansing blowing up
            a Radio Tower, and other buildings in general.</li>
        <li>Many disappearances have occurred resulting in burned corpses.</li>
        <li>Tesla Industries Falls.</li>
        <li>Ericius Enterprises comes back.</li>
        <li>Enclave Facility and Base outpost of the Lansing Area is blown up.</li>
        <li>Terror attacks stop once the man of the job 'Preacher' was
            killed and explosives were found in the church.</li>
        <li>New Michigan Republic is formed.</li>
        <li>Lansing Research Department is formed.</li>
        <li>New Michigan Republic takes the prison back,
            outfitting it with power and electrical fences.</li>
        <li>Lansing Research Department gives power to Lansing once more.</li>
        <li>Bunker38 is formed.</li>
        <li>A remnant of The Republic of Alkali is found 'Elson John'.</li>
        <li>Lansing Research Department merges with New Michigan Republic.</li>
        <li>A man named David Rowdy, along with his brother, start the popular
            Kennedy Boxing arena, drawing boxers from around the wastes.</li>
        <li>NMR wages a mini-battle with recently made Alistair federation,
            causing the destruction of their junk town, and the near death of half their men.</li>
        <li>Due to unknown reasons, Elson John dies. He is buried in NMR.</li>
        <li>Due to infighting, the leader of NMR is slain and the Republic dissolves.</li>
        <li>Mirasol Keloun, tribal healer of NMR, starts up
            The Sonne tribe in memorial of the previous leader.</li>
        <li>Many remnants of the NMR join up, including Oli Constantine.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2182</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>The Sonne tribe starts to build up in the ruins of Calco.</li>
        <li>The last NMR casualty is buried within The Sonne Tribes walls.</li>
        <li>Shadss Anlind returns to the Michigan Wastes.</li>
        <li>Jacob Reckless is killed by Shadss, in Ericius.</li>
        <li>Rumors of a lost city spreads throughout Lansing.</li>
        <li>The Sonne Tribe is nearly abandoned due to Mirasol Keloun leaving to her ancestral home.</li>
        <li>A odd new food called Nuka Fruit is invented.</li>
        <li>Johnny Reckless, son of Jacob, takes back the abandoned prison
            with a mysterious woman, after a year of emptiness.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2183</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>David Rowdy returns from his trip, bearing information of the 'Lost City of the wastes'
            giving it to Oli after he wins it, only to leave as soon as he came.</li>
        <li>A few odd robberies in strange locations occur. No trace is left of the culprit.</li>
        <li>Bunker 38 dissolves due to unexpected disappearances.</li>
        <li>Matt returns from Vault 7.</li>
        <li>Oli begins to set up for his expedition.</li>
        <li>The rebuilt radio station in NMR re-activates, playing a steady loop of classic tunes.</li>
        <li>Mirasol Keloun returns to the wastes, and re-activates The Sonne Tribe.</li>
        <li>After a mysterious series of events occur, Oli Constantine has gone without a trace,
            and a new man is being spoke about among the wastes.</li>
        <li>Lead by a man named William, The Sonne tribe becomes a Wastelander Settlement.</li>
        <li>Multiple hidden bunkers owned by Oli, Bunker 38, and a few others have recently been
            wiped off the map. Signs point to generator overloads.</li>
        <li>David Kennedy sets up shop outside of Lansing, establishing Kennedy Caravans and Courier Service.</li>
        <li>The Sonne Tribe falls once again, as Mirasol gives it to William,
            and William teams up with Johnny Reckless to make Wasteland Nations.</li>
        <li>Due to infighting, Wasteland Nations falls.</li>
        <li>The Brotherhood sets up a forward ops base, with Diane Williams.</li>
        <li>Matt returns, with a couple Vault 7 guards, and sets up Rebirth.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2184</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Random attacks come upon Rebirth, causing a strain on factory usage.</li>
        <li>BoS troops start confiscating tech from Wastelanders.</li>
        <li>A short war breaks out between BoS and Johnny Reckless, who had just taken over New Detroit.</li>
        <li>Rebirth seems to find the source of the attacks, and they cease.</li>
        <li>The Brotherhood retakes their vault.</li>
        <li>A short battle breaks out in Vardale, under the city in Vault 52.</li>
        <li>The small resistance against Vault 7, the Barnes family remnants, is crushed.</li>
        <li>Rebirth rebuilds the suburban area in Lansing.</li>
        <li>A unfortunate attack and capture reveals the truth of AIs in the Wasteland and the Paladin Williams.</li>
        <li>The attack is blamed on the BoS in Lansing and they are excommunicated and labeled rogue.</li>
        <li> A Vertibird attack takes place in Rebirth, nearly crippling the Rebirth resources.</li>
        <li>Daniel Ericius reactivates Ericius, after dormancy.</li>
        <li>A double wedding of both Cyrena and Alan, and Daniel Ericius and Kelly Swann takes place.</li>
        <li>Diane Williams is returned to the Wasteland after a near fatal crash.</li>
        <li>A extravagant halloween ball takes place in Ericius Manor.</li>
        <li>A boat pulls into Vardale Bay.</li>
        <li>After a unexpected murder, the culprit is found out to be a crazed man running the bar in the boat.</li>
        <li>David Kennedy leaves the Wasteland, and gives his wealth and Caravan to Diane Williams.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 class="lore-date subheader">2185</h4><br>
    <ul class="circle">
        <li>Diane Williams runs a new merchant faction in the wastes.</li>
        <li>Vault 52 is populated with V7 citizens.</li>
        <li>The City of Life becomes a well known mystery,
            and Fredricksons tale appears as well.</li>
        <li>Robots start appearing in Lansing.</li>
    </ul>

